'''Gserpa''' ([[Wylie transliteration|Wylie]]:''gser pa'') is an eastern [[Tibetic languages|Tibetic language]] of [[Sichuan]]. It is spoken by a few hundred or thousand people in Sêrba ([[Tibetan alphabet|Tibetan]]:གསེར་པ་; [[Wylie transliteration|Wylie]]: gser pa; [[Tibetan pinyin]]: Sêrba; [[Chinese language|Chinese]]: 色尔坝; [[pinyin]]: Sè'ěrbà) District, [[Sêrtar County]], [[Sichuan]], [[People's Republic of China|China]] and is different from the [[Amdo Tibetan language]], the dominant Tibetan language in the surrounding region.<ref name=t>N. Tournadre (2005) "L'aire linguistique tibétaine et ses divers dialectes." ''Lalies'', 2005, n°25, p.&nbsp;7–56 [http://tournadre.nicolas.free.fr/fichiers/2005-aire.pdf]</ref><ref>http://www.ling.sinica.edu.tw/eip/FILES/publish/2007.9.19.3603762.35219175.pdf</ref>
