{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox writer | name = Nagnath Kottapalle | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1948|03|29}}<ref name="whoswho">{{cite book |title=Who's who of Indian Writers |last=Dutt |first=Kartik Chandra |year=1999 |publisher=[[Sahitya Akademi]] |ref=harv |volume=1 |isbn=9788126008735 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QA1V7sICaIwC&lpg=PA665&dq=nagnath%20kottapalle&pg=PA665#v=onepage&q=nagnath%20kottapalle&f=false |page=665}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Mukhed]], Dist. [[Nanded district|Nanded]], [[Maharashtra]] | occupation = | language = [[Marathi language|Marathi]] | nationality = Indian | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = <!-- www.example.com --> | portaldisp = }} '''Nagnath Lalujirao Kottapalle''' ([[Devanagari]]: नागनाथ लालूजीराव कोत्तापल्ले) is an educationist and [[Marathi people|Marathi]] writer from [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. He was the vice chancellor of [[Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar Marathwada University]], whose seat is in [[Aurangabad, Maharashtra]]. He is elected as a president of 86th [[Akhil Bharatiya Marathi Sahitya Sammelan]] scheduled to be held at [[Chiplun]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/kottapalle-to-preside-over-86th-marathi-literary-meet/1025524/ |title=Kotapalle to preside over 86th Marathi literary meet |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=2 November 2012}}</ref>
==Early life and education== He was born on 29 March 1948 in the town of Mukhed in [[Nanded District]]. He received his B.A. (1969), M.A. (1971), and Ph.D (1980) degrees from [[Marathwada University]] in [[Marathi literature]].
==Career== Kottapalle started his career as a college lecturer in 1971 and moved up to be the head of Marathi department at [[University of Pune]]<ref name="GuptaKumar2006">{{cite book|last1=Gupta|first1=Ameeta|last2=Kumar|first2=Ashish|title=Handbook of universities|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Rs-jsaPenxYC&pg=PA688|accessdate=11 July 2011|year=2006|publisher=Atlantic Publishers & Dist|isbn=978-81-269-0608-6|pages=688–}}</ref> in 1996.
He has been a member of the following educational or literary organizations:
