'''Weert dialect''' or '''Weert Limburgish''' (natively ''Wieërts'', [[Dutch language|Standard Dutch]]: ''Weerts'' {{IPA-nl|ʋeːrts|}}) is the [[dialect|city dialect]] and variant of [[Limburgish language|Limburgish]] spoken in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] city of [[Weert]] alongside [[Dutch language|the Dutch language]] (with which it is not mutually intelligible). All of its speakers are bilingual with standard Dutch.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=107}}

It has two varieties: ''Stadsweerts'', spoken in the city centre, and the more rural dialect.{{fix|text=what is its name?|date=September 2015}}{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=107}}

