* {{IPA|/m, p, b, β/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/f, v/}} are [[Labiodental consonant|labiodental]].{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=107}}
* {{IPA|/n, l/}} are realized as postalveolar {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɲ}}, {{IPA link|ʎ}}]}} when they occur before {{IPA|/c, ɟ/}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
* {{IPA|/ɲ, c, ɟ, ʃ, ʒ/}} are marginal phonemes.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
** In the syllable onset, {{IPA|/c, ɟ, ʃ, ʒ/}} can occur only in proper names and loanwords.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
** {{IPA|/ɲ/}} occurs only intervocalically.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
* {{IPA|/ŋ, k, ɡ, x, ɣ/}} are [[Velar consonant|velar]], whereas {{IPA|/j/}} is [[Palatal consonant|palatal]].{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=107}}
** {{IPA|/ɡ/}} occurs only intervocalically. Younger speakers tend to merge it with {{IPA|/ɣ/}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
** Word-initial {{IPA|/x/}} is restricted to loanwords.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
** {{IPA|/x, ɣ/}} are realized as pre-velar {{IPA|[{{IPA link|x̟}}, {{IPA link|ɣ˖}}]}} when they are preceded or followed by a front vowel.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}
* {{IPA|/ʀ/}} is a voiced fricative trill, either uvular {{IPAblink|ʀ̝}} or pre-uvular {{IPAblink|ʀ̝|ʀ̝˖}}. The fricative component is particularly audible in the syllable [[Syllable#Coda|coda]], where a partial devoicing to {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ʀ̝̊}} ~ {{IPA link|ʀ̝̊|ʀ̝̊˖}}]}} also occurs.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=108}}

