* Most of the non-central vowels are more or less centralized, but only {{IPA|/ə/}} is phonetically central. The most strongly centralized vowel is {{IPA|/ʏ/}}, whereas the least strongly centralized vowels are {{IPA|/i, iː/}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
* Among back vowels, {{IPA|/u, uː, ʊ, oː, ɔ, ɔː/}} are rounded, whereas {{IPA|/ɑ, ɑː/}} are unrounded.
** {{IPA|/ʊ/}} is used only by older speakers.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=109}}
* Phonetically, the tense close-mid monophthongs {{IPA|/eː, øː, oː/}} are centering diphthongs {{IPA|[ëə, øə, öə]}},{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|pp=109–110}} and that is the reason for which they are illustrated on diphthong charts below.
** The first elements of {{IPA|/øː, oː/}} are centralized, but are not central enough to be labelled as central.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
** The second elements of {{IPA|/eː/}} and especially {{IPA|/oː/}} are less central ({{IPA|[e̽, ɤ̽]}}, respectively) than it is the case with other centering diphthongs, of which the second element is more like {{IPA|[ə]}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
** Before nasal consonants, {{IPA|/eː, øː/}} are monophthongized to {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɪː}}, {{IPA link|ʏː}}]}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=109}}
* The {{IPA|/ʏ/-/œ/}} and {{IPA|/ɛ/-/æ/}} contrasts seem to have begun to collapse.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=109}}{{fix|text=what about the {{IPA|/ɛː/-/æː/}} contrast?|date=October 2015}}
* {{IPA|/ʏ/}} is similar to the schwa {{IPA|/ə/}}; besides rounding, practically the only difference between those is that {{IPA|/ʏ/}} is somewhat more front and slightly higher than {{IPA|/ə/}}. Phonetically, it can be described as close-mid central rounded {{IPAblink|ɵ}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
* {{IPA|/ə/}} is mid {{IPAblink|ə}}. It occurs only in unstressed syllables.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|pp=108, 110}}
* The open-mid front vowels {{IPA|/ɛ, ɛː, œ, œː/}} are somewhat higher than open-mid {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɛ|ɛ̝}}, {{IPA link|ɛ|ɛ̝ː}}, {{IPA link|œ|œ̝}}, {{IPA link|œ|œ̝ː}}]}}, but the back open-mid vowels {{IPA|/ɔ, ɔː/}} are actually open-mid {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɔ}}, {{IPA link|ɔː}}]}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
** {{IPA|/œ/}} is realized as much more open {{IPAblink|ɶ}} when it occurs before {{IPA|/j/}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}
* {{IPA|/æ, æː/}} are best described as somewhat lowered open-mid {{IPA|[{{IPA link|æ|ɛ̞}}, {{IPA link|æ|ɛ̞ː}}]}}.{{sfnp|Heijmans|Gussenhoven|1998|p=110}}

